Package de.unifrankfurt.informatik.dbis.dia.annotation

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Condition
    Indicatates a Field in the Filter-class that this field holds the filter value for a certain Variable (Condition.name())
    Entity
    This annotation indicates an Entity-class that is used for the mapping to the RDF-datasources.
    Filter
    Indicates the filter-class.
    Prefix
    Defines a certain prefix-mapping for the DIA-context
    Prefixes
    Contains all prefix-mappings for a certain Entity-class
    Source
    Indicates the Field in the Entity-class where the source-identifier, in which this object was found is injected.
    SourceCondition  
    TriplePattern
    Stands for the Triplepattern that should be used in the SPARQL-Statement to connect the Variable to the graph.
    Variable
    Defines a variable in the context of the generated SPARQL-Statement.
